Staying still is so 2022. In 2023, Visit Wales invites you to explore the joys of Wales by undertaking one of the country’s numerous trails.
It’s an initiative that makes sense, given Wales is renowned for its walking paths, from the epic Wales Coast Path, that wraps around our entire coastline, to the famous routes snaking their way to the summit of Yr Wyddfa (Snowdon), our highest peak.&nbsp;
But of course not all trails involve donning a pair of hiking boots.

