The British royal family is celebrating Princess Charlotte's ninth birthday with a new portrait taken by her mother, Kate Middleton.
The image—shared to the official Instagram and X (formerly Twitter) accounts of the Prince and Princess of Wales on Thursday morning—shows Charlotte in a garden, smiling beside a pink flower bush.&nbsp;
“Happy 9th Birthday, Princess Charlotte!,” the caption reads. “Thank you for all of the kind messages today.”&nbsp;
The young princess is William and Kate’s second of three children, alongside her older brother Prince George, 10, and younger brother Prince Louis, 6.

